This paper is primarily focused on the usability of password strategies, which is a key concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the study involves human participants and their ability to mentally compute passwords, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY), as well as software engineering (cs.SE) and information systems (cs.SI) in terms of developing and testing password strategies.
